# React Components

## Structure

1. Imports → types → component → (optional) subcomponents
2. One component per file for route-level and shared UI
3. Extract hooks when logic is reused or clutters the component

## Composition Over Configuration

```tsx
// ✅ Composable, predictable
<Card>
  <CardHeader title="Portfolio" />
  <CardBody>{children}</CardBody>
</Card>

// ❌ Prop explosion
<Card title="Portfolio" showHeader showFooter variant="lg" ... />
```

## State

- Lift state only as high as needed
- Prefer URL/search params for shareable UI state (filters, tabs)
- Avoid `useEffect` for derived data — compute inline or use `useMemo` sparingly

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML: `nav`, `main`, `section`, `button` vs `div onClick`
- Every interactive element needs a visible focus state
- Images: meaningful `alt`; decorative images use `alt=""`
- External links: `target="_blank"` + `rel="noopener noreferrer"`

## Lists & Keys

- Use stable, unique keys (not array index for reorderable lists)
